Vice President Biden met with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko at the United Nations General Assembly in New York. Biden congratulated Poroshenko on completing the IMF review and informed him that all policy steps have been taken to proceed with the issuance of Ukraine's third U.S. sovereign loan guarantee of up to $1 billion. They agreed that these milestones show Ukraine's progress on reform. Biden emphasized the need for Ukraine's leadership to speed up reforms in the energy and justice sectors and stressed the importance of fully implementing the Minsk Agreements.